The Finance Ministry auctioned 280 billionyen of four-year government notes, the first auction of fiscal1987 which started on April 1.    The coupon was set at 3.7 pct, a record low for anygovernment note and below the 3.8 pct set on the last two-yearnotes, auctioned in February.    Today's issue was the first for four-year notes since lastMay, which produced an average price of 99.79, average yield of4.561 pct and a coupon of 4.5 pct, the Ministry said.    The auction results will be announced tomorrow afternoon. REUTER&#3;